    "content": "**Geopolitiks Snacks** — April 9, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🔫 Trump Adds \"Who's Arming Iran\" to the Tariff Menu\n\nOne day after brokering a ceasefire with Tehran, Trump announced 50% tariffs on any country supplying Iran with weapons. The targets are Russia and China. The legal authority is unclear.\n\n- **The announcement:** Via Truth Social on April 8 — any nation \"supplying military weapons to Iran\" faces immediate 50% tariffs, no exclusions or exemptions. Russia and China deny supplying anything. The specific legal mechanism is unspecified, a detail that matters since the Supreme Court struck down Trump's IEEPA authority in February.\n- **The offer:** In the same breath, Trump said the U.S. would \"work closely\" with Iran on sanctions relief and tariffs. The carrot and the stick — except the stick may currently be unconstitutional.\n\n*Tariffs announced via Truth Social, no clear legal basis, targeting countries that deny the premise. A new era of sanctions law.*\n\n**Sources:** [CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/04/08/trump-threatens-tariffs-countries-supplying-weapons-iran-ceasefire.html) | [Al Jazeera](https://www.aljazeera.com/economy/2026/4/8/trump-threatens-50-tariffs-on-countries-that-supply-iran-with-weapons) | [Yahoo Finance](https://finance.yahoo.com/economy/policy/article/trump-tariffs-live-updates-trump-announces-50-tariffs-on-any-country-supplying-weapons-to-iran-223100659.html)\n\n---\n\n## ⛽ Europe Has Until April 20. Then Things Get Interesting.\n\nThe Iran war and Hormuz closure have severed Europe's LNG and oil supply chains. Russia's envoy says reserves run dry by April 20. Fifteen EU member states are already in critical territory.\n\n- **The numbers:** Gas prices up 70%. Oil up 60%. Europe's fossil fuel import bill jumped €14 billion in one month. EU-wide averages remain above the 90-day mandatory minimum — but 15 member states are at critical levels. Romania's diesel reserves: 20.2 days, against a required 90.\n- **The deadline:** Kirill Dmitriev, Russia's presidential investment envoy, says the last Hormuz shipments reach Europe on April 11, with total depletion by April 20. The EU is exploring rationing and emergency reserve releases. The European Commissioner advised member states to \"prepare for a prolonged energy crisis.\"\n\n*Russia warning Europe about running out of fuel is either a public service announcement or a sales pitch. Possibly both.*\n\n**Sources:** [EU Pravda](https://eu.news-pravda.com/eu/2026/04/04/183553.html) | [European Conservative](https://europeanconservative.com/articles/news/frances-fuel-shortages-expose-europes-new-energy-crisis/) | [Atlantic Council](https://www.atlanticcouncil.org/dispatches/how-the-iran-war-could-trigger-a-european-energy-crisis/)\n\n---\n\n## 🕊️ The Iran Talks Are Moving to Islamabad. Nobody Agrees on What Was Agreed.\n\nThe U.S.-Iran ceasefire is holding — for now. Both sides claimed victory, the next round is in Pakistan, and Trump is floating a nuclear deal as the endgame.\n\n- **What's happening:** Pakistan invited U.S. and Iranian delegations to Islamabad for April 10 talks. Iran's Supreme National Security Council declared the ceasefire a \"victory.\" Trump called Iran's 10-point counter-proposal \"a workable basis\" and signaled U.S. readiness to discuss sanctions relief.\n- **The endgame:** Trump has indicated the goal is a new nuclear agreement. Iran's conditions have not been published. Both parties are negotiating through the fog of a two-week ceasefire that both parties claim to have won.\n\n*Both sides agreed to a ceasefire. Both sides declared victory. Peace talks are in Islamabad. Normal Tuesday.*\n\n**Sources:** [NBC News](https://www.nbcnews.com/world/iran/live-blog/live-updates-iran-war-trump-deadline-hormuz-infrastructure-ceasefire-rcna267039) | [PBS](https://www.pbs.org/newshour/world/irans-supreme-national-security-council-says-it-has-accepted-two-week-ceasefire-in-the-war) | [Visa Verge](https://www.visaverge.com/news/trump-threatens-iran-arms-suppliers-with-tariffs-offers-nuclear-talks/)"
